image_cropper
    heuristic model for cropping images
    - image_cropper.py         
        main cropping script
        usage: python image_cropper.py --out [output_dir]  --in <input_image_path_or_dir>  [--debug any_t]
    - heuristic_to_yolo.py     
        use image_cropper.py to generate yolo format labels from images
        usage: python heuristic_to_yolo.py --src <src_dir> [--dst <dst_dir>]
    - cleanup_dataset.py       
        cleanup script for removing bad images from ai dataset
        usage: python cleanup_dataset.py [--dry-run] >]
    - manual_cropper.py        
        manual cropping script
        usage: python manual_cropper.py --src <src_dir> [--dst <dst_dir>]

aimage_cropper

    notes on using yolo:

    check if CUDA available via cmd line:
        python - <<'PY'
        import torch
        print("CUDA available:", torch.cuda.is_available())
        if torch.cuda.is_available():
            print("GPU name:", torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))
        PY
    
    train model (with nano yolo model):
        yolo detect train model=yolov8n.pt data=aimage_cropper/dataset/data.yml device=0 epochs=30 imgsz=640 batch=-1

    sanity check validation:
        yolo detect val   model=./runs/detect/train3/weights/best.pt  data=aimage_cropper/dataset/data.yml imgsz=896


    use AI model for image cropping on set of labeled images
    - aimage_cropper.py        
        runs cropping on set of labeled images with some pretrained model
        usage:
        python yolo_autocrop.py --model runs/detect/train/weights/best.pt --src "C:\pics" --dst "./autocrops"
        python yolo_autocrop.py --model best.pt --src ./raw --dst ./out --conf 0.2 --iou 0.6 --imgsz 640 --pad 0.03 --device 0
        python yolo_autocrop.py --model best.pt --src ./raw --dst ./out --on-miss skip --flatten --overwrite
